  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CSR-facility. Mellemfolkeligt Samvirke (Action Aid). Tax Justice: tax and corporate social responsibility</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The aim of the project is to contribute to the realization of the strategic priority that Mellemfolkeligt Samvirke (MS) og ActionAid (AA) have taken in terms of promoting enterprises&apos; contribution to the tax base in developing countries. MS and AA use considerable resources to achieve that in developing countries. This will only succeed if richer countries take upon initiatives that make companies pay more tzs. Thus, the aim of the project is to make the Danish Government become a leading country in trelation to tax and get companies to recognize tax as an issue for their CSR work. Realization of this will happen through voluntary commetted young people who raise a public debate that puts the issue on the agendaand creates a popular pressure. the grant is for a two year period from 2014 to 2015.</narrative>
  </description>
